caption.text:
🚨JUST IN: North Korea warns the US and European Union against joining Israel’s war with Iran, condemning Israeli strikes as state-sponsored terrorism risking an all-out Middle East war.

Pyongyang expressed “serious concern” over Israel’s attacks on Iran, calling them a “crime against humanity” and accusing Israel, backed by the US and West, of destabilizing regional and global peace. North Korea urged Western powers to stop “fanning the flames of war,” warning their involvement could push the conflict into an uncontrollable catastrophic phase amid ongoing missile exchanges. The statement reflects North Korea’s growing alignment with Iran and Russia in the escalating crisis.
